com.projecttango.unibw.graphmapper.graph

Class Entrypoint

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.projecttango.unibw.graphmapper.graph.Entrypoint

  • public class Entrypoint
extends java.lang.Object

    A Entrypoint is a connection between two hallways. It can be a simple door or stairs or a lift.

    In this version the user have to create a entrypoint for each level a lift can reach and connect the entrypoints of each level. A entrypoint can be seen as the edges of the navigation graph / network.

    This class was created by Konstantin Klinger on 25.04.16. Added changes of Google's Okul update from June 9th (13.06.2016).

    Version:
    2.0
    Author:
    Konstantin Klinger

        public void addConnection(float[] pos,
                 int id)
        This function adds a new connection to this entrypoint. It adds the position as a float[] value to the mPositionToList and adds the id of the connected hallway as a int to the mHallwayToIDList.
        Parameters:

        id - (id of the connected hallway)
